# Web App

## Purpose

The `web` app is the public marketing and product website.
It is not the merchant storefront runtime (`apps/storefront`).

## Structure

```text
apps/web/src/
├── app/
│   ├── [lang]/
│   │   ├── layout.tsx
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   └── manifest.ts
├── components/
│   ├── app/
│   ├── layout/
│   └── shared/
├── lib/
│   └── i18n.ts
├── env.ts
└── proxy.ts
```

## Routes

### Localized Home Page

**Location**: `apps/web/src/app/[lang]/page.tsx`

Public home page with welcome content and features.

### Layout

**Location**: `apps/web/src/app/[lang]/layout.tsx`

Root layout with providers and metadata.

## Components

### Organization

Components are organized by feature and shared layout concerns:

```text
components/
  ├── app/
  ├── layout/
  └── shared/
```

### File Naming

- **kebab-case** for file names
- **PascalCase** for component names

### Component Pattern

```typescript
// apps/web/src/components/layout/header.tsx
"use client";

import Link from "next/link";

export function Header() {
  return (
    <header>
      <nav>
        <Link href="/">Home</Link>
      </nav>
    </header>
  );
}
```

## Imports

### Path Aliases

- `@/` - `apps/web/src/`
- `@dukkani/*` - Package imports

### Import Pattern

```typescript
// Local imports (use @/)
import { Header } from "@/components/layout/header";

// Package imports
import { Button } from "@dukkani/ui/components/button";
import { env } from "@dukkani/env";
```

## Dependencies

- `next` - Next.js framework
- `react` - React library
- `@dukkani/ui` - UI components
- `@dukkani/env` - Environment variables
- `next-intl` - i18n routing and locale handling

## Best Practices

- Use server components by default
- Add `"use client"` only when needed for interactivity
- Keep marketing and acquisition concerns in `web`, not storefront commerce logic
- Use UI components from `@dukkani/ui`
- Keep components simple and focused
- Use path aliases for cleaner imports
